{"cursor":"2968","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\nAn 'insurance bond' (or 'investment bond') is a single premium life assurance\npolicy for the purposes of investment.\n\nDue to tax laws they are a common form of investment in the UK and some\noffshore centres.\n\nTraditionally insurance bonds were with-profits policies and were often called\nwith-profit(s) bonds. Since the introduction of unitised insurance funds they\nhave often been marketed as unit-linked bonds or investment bonds.\n","linknr":118,"url":"Insurance_bond","recorded":1362555827,"links":17,"instances":[],"pdf":[],"categories":["Financial services","Investment"],"headings":["Why invest in an insurance bond?","Range of investment funds","History","See also","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/6c/Wiki_letter_w.svg/23px-Wiki_letter_w.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/29/ThreeCoins.svg/40px-ThreeCoins.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[],"members":[],"related":["Life_assurance","Investment","Tax_law","United_Kingdom","Offshore_investment","With-profits_policy","Unitised_insurance_fund","Unit_trust","AXA_Sun_Life","Corporate_bond","Equities","Unit_Trusts","Collective_Investment_Scheme","Life_assurance","Investment","With-profits_policy","Unitised_insurance_fund"]}